{
  "name": "Chakra Threads",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Non%20Elemental.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">It takes the form of strings that extend from your fingertips</span>. The threads lasts for the duration or until you dismiss it as an action. The threads vanishes if it is ever more than 30 feet away from you or if you dismiss the jutsu. You can use your action to control the hand.</p><p>You can use the threads to manipulate an object, open an unlocked door or container, stow or retrieve an item from an open container, or pour the contents out of a vial. You can move the threads up to 30 feet each time you use it. The threads can't attack, activate chakra items, or carry more than 10 * your Proficiency Bonus pounds</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">At 9th level, losing the ability to mold chakra does not prevent you from using your Chakra Threads.</span></p>",
